I made these for my co-workers birthday. I took the recommendation of finely grating an apple to substitute for part of the oil to healthy it up a little bit. One small apple was almost half a cup, and for the other 1/4 cup-ish I used butter because I didn't have vegetable oil. The cupcakes were fantastic! Moist, dense, more like banana bread than a cake. I substituted a no-powdered-sugar cream cheese frosting for the orange glaze, because cream cheese frosting is so, so, so good; and I didn't bother with the candied carrots since they seemed like a giant pain. But the cupcakes... so good.

