I made this with butter rather than oil, and did half the cakes with gluten free flour. All looked and smelled the same, though the texture of those with GF flour wasn't so good, and the taste of the soda and BP was a bit too strong - I should have adjusted these down. I did the icing as suggested though without the carrot curls. Overall the flavour was very good - but not outstanding. The texture was definitely too dry, so perhaps oil is better than butter for this. The icing was easy - I just added juice til the consistency seemed right, so they only needed one coat. I used ordinary sized muffin tins rather than jumbo ones - with these, the recipe made 15 cupcakes. Again, I wonder whether a larger muffin tin would result in a moister texture?

