Rating: 0
These cupcakes are marvelous!! They taste like carrot cake at first and then after a second it's an orange sensation! They are perfect texture too. (BONUS!!) I made a few changes though. One viewer said that they were a bit too oily. So instead of measuring the full 3/4 cup of the oil, I measured 1/3 cup, and then the rest of the way with applesauce. This complimented the "holiday spice taste" in them and cut down the fat. Also, instead of using orange juice for the icing, I used tangerine juice. This was great, because I thought the confectioners sugar would be too sweet, so I used the tangerine juice to add a tiny bit of bitterness. Also, if you like lots of icing, something my mom did was dip the cupcakes in the icing once, let them dry, and then dip them again. This created a nice thick layer of icing. I would say one layer of icing is prettier though if you're bringing these to a party. I definitely recommend this recipe!

